  "title" : "What are good Java date-chooser Swing GUI widgets?",
  "body" : "<p>What are good Java Swing date-chooser components? So far I've only really found these 2:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://toedter.com/jcalendar/\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>JCalendar</code></a> - this one is pretty good as it uses the underlying look and feel.</li>\n<li><code>JXMonthView</code> in the <a href=\"https://java.net/projects/swingx\" rel=\"noreferrer\">SwingX</a> project - not so good as it uses its own look and feel</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Both of these look a bit clunky when compared with some I've seen on web-pages. For example, it might be nice to see <em>multiple months</em> at the same time. Does anyone know of any other good widgets out there?</p>\n"
}